description:
These were specially recorded interviews from the Salford recording of I'm Sorry I Haven't A Clue - Live on Stage.

This is a tribute to the late and great 'Sir' Humphrey Littleton, who died 19 days after the making of this show. 

He actually turned down his offer of a knighthood but no better tribute than to remember him at his best!

Recorded from the Lyric Theatre, Lowry Centre, Salford on Sunday 6th April 2008, this is I'm Sorry I Haven't A Clue - Live: The self-styled antidote to panel games.

Starring Humphrey Littleton, Graeme Garden, Tim Brooke-Taylor, Barry Cryer and Jeremy Hardy with Colin Sell at the piano and scorer, Samantha.

Produced and directed by Jon Naismith. An edited version was broadcast on 13th September 2008 on BBC4.

(c) Ransom Entertainment 2008 for which no copyright infringement is intended. Any problems with this posting, please let me know and I will immediately remove it, otherwise I post this both as a tribute to "Humph" and as a long time lover of this great show. If you enjoyed this, please rate and comment. Thanks.
